        <div class="boxContent">
          <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><h1 style="text-align: center;"><span class="pageheading">SAG-AFTRA ONLINE POLICIES<br />Updated August 8, 2012</span></h1>
<p>Thank you for visiting sagaftra.org.  This site and all related domains – including, but not limited to, sag-aftra.com, sag-aftra.org, sag.org, aftra.org, sag.com and aftra.com – (collectively, the “Site”) are owned by Screen Actors Guild-American Federation of Television and Radio Artists (“SAG-AFTRA,” the “Union,”or “us”).  This document contains the Terms of Use and Privacy Policy Including Privacy Policy For Children Under the Age of 13 for the Site (collectively, the “Terms” or the “Agreement”).  SAG-AFTRA shall be free to change these Terms at any time by posting the changes on the Site without any individual notice to you, except as otherwise required by law.  Your use of the Site after any such change is posted will be deemed to be acceptance of such change. It is your responsibility to review these Terms of Use periodically, and if at any time you find these Terms of Use unacceptable, you must immediately leave the Site and cease all use of the Site.</p>
<p>Table of Contents (Click to view text of document):</p>
<ul><li><a href="/privacy-policy-terms-use/#terms">SAGAFTRA.org Terms of Use</a></li>
<li><a href="/privacy-policy-terms-use/#policy">SAGAFTRA.org Privacy Policy</a></li>
<li><a href="/privacy-policy-terms-use/#under13">SAG-AFTRA Privacy Policy in Regard to Children Under the Age of 13</a></li>
<li><a href="/files/sag-aftra_coppa_policy_form.pdf">Consent of Parent or Legal Guardian</a></li>
</ul><p>If you are not a SAG-AFTRA member, please be aware that some portions of the Site are available for the benefit of SAG-AFTRA members only and are not available to non-members.  You may be denied access to certain portions of the Site if you are not a member in good standing of SAG-AFTRA.  </p>
<p>SAG-AFTRA is a non-profit, non-commercial organization and the Site is a non-commercial web site or online service.  In an attempt to comply with various laws related to privacy policies, including but not limited to the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”), and to set a good example for others, SAG-AFTRA has created the enclosed Privacy Policy and the Privacy Policy in Regard to Children Under the Age of 13.  Such efforts by SAG-AFTRA shall not be deemed to be a waiver of any rights or defenses otherwise available to SAG-AFTRA.</p>
<h3><em><strong>If you are 18 years of age or older:</strong></em></h3>
<ul><li>You agree that by using the Site you represent that you are at least 18 years old and that you are legally able to enter into this Agreement.</li>
<li>By using the Site and by clicking on the “I Accept” button below, you are creating a legal and binding agreement between you  and SAG-AFTRA (the “SAG-AFTRA” or “us”), the owner of the Site, confirming your agreement with all of the Terms. </li>
</ul><h3><em><strong>If you are under 13 years of age:</strong></em></h3>
<ul><li>You must provide the written verifiable consent of a parent or guardian to these Terms as a condition to your admission to and use of the Site.  You will not be able to use or access the Site until you do so.  </li>
<li>Please have your parent or guardian complete the Consent of Parent or Guardian form linked above and return it to us as instructed on the form.  </li>
</ul><h3><em><strong>If you are 13 years of age or older but under 18 years of age:</strong></em></h3>
<ul><li>You must provide the written verifiable consent of a parent or guardian to these Terms or confirmation that you are an emancipated minor at least 13 years old as a condition to your admission to and use of the Site.  </li>
<li>SAG-AFTRA may grant you access to the Site on a provisional basis for a limited time from the date you first register, after which time your access may be suspended if you have not yet provided SAG-AFTRA with the required parental consents.</li>
<li>Please have your parent or guardian complete the Consent of Parent or Guardian form listed above and return it to us as instructed on the form.  If you are an emancipated minor, please complete this form for yourself and provide the required documentation in support of your status.</li>
</ul><h2><strong><a title="terms" name="terms" id="terms"></a>SAGAFTRA.ORG TERMS OF USE</strong></h2>
<ol><li><strong>Changes to the Site.</strong> SAG-AFTRA may add or change the content of the Site at any time and any additions or changes shall be automatically deemed covered by these Terms.  SAG-AFTRA may terminate or suspend the Site or your access to the Site, in whole or in part, at any time.  No such actions shall be deemed a breach or violation of this Agreement by SAG-AFTRA.  SAG-AFTRA shall not be obligated to provide individual notice to you of any changes to the Site unless otherwise required by law.</li>
<li><strong> Posting User Content.</strong> You may not use the Site or post anything to the Site unless you are at least 13 years of age.  If you desire to use the Site or post to the Site and you are under 13 years of age, you will be required to provide written consent from your parent or legal guardian.  <a href="/privacy-policy-terms-use/#under13">Click here for additional information</a>.  You are responsible for everything you post or transmit to or through the Site, including, for example, any photographs, audio clips, descriptions, biographical material, contact information, experience or other information you provide (“User Content”).  User Content shall include all information and materials posted on or through the Site under your user ID.   You agree to update all User Content to keep it current and accurate at all times.  Some information you post on the Site, such as your iActor profile, is not private and may be accessed and viewed by others.  SAG-AFTRA is not responsible for how such information is used by third parties.  When using Site features like iActor, we recommend that you not disclose your home address, home telephone number or other personal information you may not want generally disclosed.  Consider posting the contact information for your agent or manager instead.  If you do not have an agent or manager, consider obtaining a post office box and an answering service.</li>
<li><strong>Inappropriate Content; Suspension or Termination of Account.</strong> You agree not to upload, download, display, perform, transmit, or otherwise distribute any content that (a) is libelous, defamatory, obscene, pornographic, abusive, threatening, or otherwise inappropriate for the Site’s users; (b) advocates or encourages conduct that could constitute a criminal offense, give rise to civil liability, or otherwise violate any applicable local, state, national, or foreign law or regulation; (c) advertises or otherwise solicits funds or is a solicitation for goods or services; or (d) infringes on the copyright, trademark, right of publicity or other intellectual property rights of others.  SAG-AFTRA reserves the right to suspend or terminate your receipt, transmission, or other distribution of any such material using the Site, and, if applicable, to delete any such material from its servers. SAG-AFTRA may, in its discretion, suspend or terminate your account for any violation of these Terms.  It is SAG-AFTRA's policy, in its discretion, to disable and/or terminate the accounts of users who may infringe or repeatedly infringe the copyrights or other intellectual property rights of others.  SAG-AFTRA further reserves the right to suspend or terminate your access to some or all of the Site if you fail to timely pay your SAG-AFTRA dues or if you are no longer a member of SAG-AFTRA in good standing.  SAG-AFTRA intends to cooperate fully with any law enforcement officials or agencies in the investigation of any violation of these Terms or of any applicable laws.</li>
